Organisers of the Mark D Ball Basketball Championship have announced that top music acts will perform at the rejuvenated basketball championship in Abuja. Director of Media for Mark D Ball Basketball Championship, Kingsley Aigbonoga, said Innocent Idibia (2Baba) will lead other top music stars to light up Abuja during the championship. He disclosed that Joel El, Magnito, Ice Prince, Goya Menor, Rayce and Chuddy K will all perform live at the championship. “The Mark D Ball Championship is a complete package as we are mixing sports and entertainment together. “Beyond the playing basketball, the organisers are bringing 2Baba, Joel El, Magnito, Ice Prince, Rayce, Goya Menor, Chuddy K and many more to spice up the championship with their live performances. “Also, we are bringing some other special guest celebrities. “Certainly, Abuja will come alive,” Aigbonoga stated. Mark D Ball Basketball Championship dunks off at the MKO Abiola Stadium, Abuja this weekend with 16 teams participating.